parties.raw_snippet: This Development Agreement (“this Agreement”) is entered into and effective as of September 30, 2019 (“Effective Date”) by and between Howmedica Osteonics Corp., a New Jersey corporation, also known as Stryker Orthopaedics (“Stryker”), and Conformis, Inc., a Delaware corporation having a principal place of business located at 600 Technology Park Drive, Billerica, MA 01821 (“Conformis”).
parties.reasoning: The opening recitals identify the contracting parties by name and corporate form; this sentence explicitly states the two parties to the Agreement.

contract_type.raw_snippet: Stryker desires that Conformis develop, in accordance with the R&D Program, certain Patient-Specific Instrumentation to be used with the current version of the Off-The-Shelf Knee Implant offered under the trademark Triathlon (such Patient-Specific Instrumentation as so developed, the “KIB Product”).
contract_type.reasoning: The core economic substance is that Conformis will develop patient-specific instrumentation for Stryker under an R&D program with milestone payments — i.e., a development arrangement. The recital describing Stryker's desire that Conformis develop the KIB Product captures the primary purpose.

agreement_date.raw_snippet: This Development Agreement (“this Agreement”) is entered into and effective as of September 30, 2019 (“Effective Date”) by and between Howmedica Osteonics Corp., a New Jersey corporation, also known as Stryker Orthopaedics (“Stryker”), and Conformis, Inc., a Delaware corporation having a principal place of business located at 600 Technology Park Drive, Billerica, MA 01821 (“Conformis”).
agreement_date.reasoning: The clause states the Agreement is "entered into and effective as of September 30, 2019" which is the express agreement/contract date language.

effective_date.raw_snippet: This Development Agreement (“this Agreement”) is entered into and effective as of September 30, 2019 (“Effective Date”) by and between Howmedica Osteonics Corp., a New Jersey corporation, also known as Stryker Orthopaedics (“Stryker”), and Conformis, Inc., a Delaware corporation having a principal place of business located at 600 Technology Park Drive, Billerica, MA 01821 (“Conformis”).
effective_date.reasoning: The same clause explicitly labels September 30, 2019 as the "Effective Date."

expiration_date.raw_snippet: The term of this Agreement shall begin as of the Effective Date and continue until Acceptance of all Deliverables for Milestones #1 and #2 pursuant to Section 3.4 and completion of Milestone #3, unless earlier terminated under Section 8.2, as provided for under the Other Agreements, or as mutually agreed by the Parties.
expiration_date.reasoning: Section 8.1 defines the term/expiration in relative terms — it runs from the Effective Date until specified milestone acceptances and completion of Milestone #3, subject to earlier termination. This is the contract's express term/expiration language.
expiration_date.normalized_value: begin as of the Effective Date and continue until Acceptance of all Deliverables for Milestones #1 and #2 pursuant to Section 3.4 and completion of Milestone #3, unless earlier terminated under Section 8.2, as provided for under the Other Agreements, or as mutually agreed by the Parties.

governing_law.raw_snippet: This Agreement shall be governed and construed in accordance with the laws of New York State (without regard to the conflict of laws provisions thereof).
governing_law.reasoning: Section 10.7 explicitly states the governing law as the laws of New York State.

notice_period.reasoning: The contract contains no clause requiring advance notice to prevent automatic renewal (there is no automatic renewal/renewal-prevention language). Term is tied to milestone completion and termination provisions rather than an auto-renewal mechanism.

renewal_term.reasoning: There is no renewal or automatic renewal clause in the Agreement; the term is defined to run until milestone completion and may be terminated earlier. No renewal term is specified.
